<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 3:02AM EDT  by NWS Cleveland</headline>
<description>...Valley Fog Reducing Visibilities...
Valley fog in the favored areas along with a few patches of dense
fog will persist through sunrise this morning. Visibilities in the
dense fog will be reduced to less than a quarter mile. Motorists
should exercise caution when encountering the fog and allow extra
distance between their vehicle and the one in front of them.
The fog is expected to impact the morning commute and should
dissipate by 9 AM this morning.</description>
